  "value": 0.62,
  "rationale": "Every quantified reference-class datapoint found (TryBuildCo ~0.1%, Tractian ~0.001%, POC acceptance failure 30%) sits below the curated band, and the timeframe mismatch between the benchmark definition (3–5 yr) and the YAM window (12 mo) is documented in the digest, not conjectured [evidence revision: Two independent benchmark sources explicitly define SOM over a 1–2 or 1–3 year window, directly confirming the timeframe-mismatch premise that a mid-band factor applied to a 12-month YAM window borrows years 2–3. The ecodesign conformity requirement is confirmed by primary regulation. However, no source provides certification-duration months or a quantified realized Year-1 share for a hardware entrant, so the exact 5x magnitude claim remains partly inferential — modest upward revision only.]",
  "basis": "evidence",
  "revisedFrom": 0.6
 },
